## Release 4.2.0

### Admin

The admin sshd server supoports public key and password authentication mechanisms. 
Some facilities have cyber security policies that explicitly disallow these mechanisms. 
This release adds kerberos authentication mechanism to admin sshd server and 
introduces ability to enable specific authentication mechanism(s) to conform to 
different security policies. The following configuration variables 
have been added to control the behavior:

```
admin.ssh.authn.enabled = password,publickey
```

(by default the same existing mechanisms are enabled - password and public key). If kerberos 
authentication is chosen there is a second configuration variable pointing at location
of keytab file on your system:

```
admin.ssh.authn.kerberos.keytab-file = /etc/krb5.keytab
```



